  <description type="morphology">Trees  to 40m; trunk to 1.5m diam.; crown conic.  Bark  charcoal gray to reddish brown, scaly and deeply fissured.  Twigs  yellow-brown, glabrous to densely pubescent.  Buds  oblong, 3--4mm.  Leaves  10--25(--30)mm, mostly spreading in all directions from twigs, curved toward twig apex, thickened centrally along midline, somewhat rounded or 4-angled in cross section, both surfaces glaucous, with ±inconspicuous stomatal bands; margins entire.  Seed cones  oblong-cylindric, 3--6 × 1.5--3cm; scales broadly fan-shaped, 8--l5 × 8--15mm, apex rounded to pointed. 2 n =24.</description>
